<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-222-926  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 222 926.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 24 1989 n312 p111(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>WordPerfect breaking from mold with multiplatform line. (softwarepackages) (company profile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gross, June.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>WordPerfect Corp's strategy includes making its software availableon multi-vendor platforms.andP;  WordPerfect, which delivers 85 percentof company revenue, runs on DEC VAX-VMS, Data General, IBM 370,Commodore International Amiga, Atari, Apple II, and AppleMacintosh systems.andP;  The same strategy applies to WordPerfectOffice, an electronic-mail system introduced in fall 1988, andPlanPerfect spreadsheet software.andP;  WordPerfect is betting thatcompanies want the same look and feel, plus file transfer withoutconversion, for software running on micro- to mainframe computersand across vendor platforms.andP;  The overwhelming majority ofWordPerfect sales are for DOS platforms but the $6 million inVAX-VMS and $2 million in Data General sales in 1988 generatedlike amounts of DOS business.andP;  The privately held firm has astrong growth record and is likely to reach $240 to $300 millionsales in 1989, giving it a third-place market share.andP;  Analysts saya public offering is unlikely.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   WordPerfect Corp. (management).andO;Topic:     Company ProfileSoftware PublishersWord ProcessingMultivendor SystemsMarketingOffice Automation.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>